peekToken

public ProlTokenizer.ProlTokenizerResult peekToken(ProlReader reader,
                                                   KnowledgeBase voc)
                                            throws java.io.IOException
Peek the next token from the incomming stream. The token will be read and available but it will not be removed from the incomming stream.

Parameters:
reader - the reader to get the incomming token, must not be null
voc - the knowledge base which will be used for the operation, must not be null
Returns:
a read token as a ProlTokenizerResult, or null if there is not any token in the stream
Throws:
java.io.IOException - it will be throws if there is any transport problem
